	Aniston show    
	 London, Oct. 27 (PTI): Actress Jennifer Aniston, who shot to fame with her role in the TV comedy Friends, will again appear on the small screen with Oprah Winfrey.      
	The actress will produce and star with Winfrey in a weekly late-night programme which will be broadcast on the Oprah Winfrey Network, reports the Sunday Express.      
	Anistons friendship with comedienne Chelsea Handler, who fronts her own TV talk show, inspired her to take on the project. Jen became fascinated with the format after spending time with Chelsea. When she saw Oprah she mentioned that it would be fun to do a chat show and Oprah seized the moment and suggested they front one together for her new network, a source said.    
	Wild Jolie    
	 London (PTI): Actress Angelina Jolie slept with her mothers boyfriend when she was 16 years old, claims a new unauthorised biography. Writer Andrew Morton has alleged that the Lara Croft star spent a night with her mother Marcheline Bertrands live-in partner and later confessed the act to her, reports Now magazine. As a result, the French actress ended her relationship with her boyfriend and struggled hard to keep her ties with Jolie alive.     
	Bridge act    
	 New York (Reuters): Actress Scarlett Johansson will make her Broadway debut starring in a revival of American playwright Arthur Millers drama A View from the Bridge, the shows organisers said on Monday. Johansson, 24, will appear on the Great White Way opposite actor Liev Schreiber in the drama set in 1950s America about a Brooklyn dockyard worker obsessed with his 17-year-old niece, to be played by Johansson.    
	Lohan pay    
	Los Angeles (PTI): Lindsay Lohan, who quit acting to make a career in the world of fashion, is reportedly not getting paid for the clothes she designed for Emmanuelle Ungaro. Lohan worked on designs with the fashion houses new head designer Estrella Archs for three weeks, but was given 90,000 worth of free clothes in place of payment.    
	Renee hurt    
	London (PTI): Actress Renee Zellweger has reportedly broken up with actor Bradley Cooper as he did not want to be tied down with a relationship. The actress, who won an Oscar for her role in Cold Mountain, began dating the actor earlier this year and is distraught after Coopers decision.                                                                                                                                                                        
